content: This is the best i have seen so far. It works completely offline, you don't have to download questions after installation like most other junks out there. The diagrams shows and is very clear, English started with Comprehension passage unlike some that remove it. This should be a 10 star app. What I love most about it is not just the simplicity and good graphics, the software allows you to select the topics you want questions from, this help students read according to syllabus. Finally they nailed it by making available 3 modes. A student can decide to use study mode, practise mode, and mock mode and all these modes have features that give learner satisfaction. With this you can never write Jamb or Waec twice.May God bless the developers of this app

The app is fair but not what I expect, in the visual design, it is good, but for the random mode practice, it does not really model anything good. Take for example the close passage in the English is poorly presented while the comprehension passages are not even include. Honestly MS_CBT is the best of all the cbts in terms of random question practice if u practice it in the exam mode. It really does model random questions even for closed passages and comprehension passages in English. Kudos to the author.
replyContent: Thanks for your views. But TestDriller is designed to allow users to practise questions on yearly bases. We believe it will help users take a complete set of questions and verify the authenticity of our questions. We don't have RANDOM MODE but allow users to select RANDOM YEAR (questions from all the years) which is useful for practising by topic.
